# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# cni-net-lab — Lab Secrets
# Copy to lab.secrets (already in .gitignore) and fill in real values.
# This file is loaded automatically by load_lab_env() alongside lab.env.
#
# Values here can contain special characters (tokens, passwords) safely —
# load_lab_env() parses without shell eval.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# ── NGINX Plus (Module 2+) ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# JWT from MyF5 portal — used to pull from private-registry.nginx.com
# NGINX_JWT=

# ── BIG-IP CIS (Module 3) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Credentials for the BIG-IP management API
# BIGIP_USER=admin
# BIGIP_PASS=
# BIGIP_MGMT_IP=

# ── DockerHub (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Avoids anonymous pull rate limits when caching images
# DOCKERHUB_USER=
# DOCKERHUB_PASS=

# ── Argo CD ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Custom admin password (username is always 'admin'). Set this to pick your own
# password instead of the random one Argo CD generates on first install.
# Plaintext here — install-argocd.sh bcrypt-hashes it before handing it to Helm,
# so it is never stored in the cluster in the clear. Requires 'htpasswd'
# (apache2-utils) or the python3 'bcrypt' module on the host.
# Re-applied on every 'task argocd:install', so it always wins over UI changes.
# ARGOCD_ADMIN_PASSWORD=

# Repository credentials — REQUIRED if this repo is PRIVATE. Argo CD clones the
# repo to pull manifests; without a credential a private repo leaves the root
# Application stuck at Sync=Unknown with no child apps. Use a GitHub Personal
# Access Token with read access to the repo as the password (username is ignored
# for PAT auth, so the default 'git' is fine). 'task argocd:bootstrap' turns
# these into an Argo CD repository Secret.
# ARGOCD_REPO_USERNAME=git
# ARGOCD_REPO_PASSWORD=

# ── Gitea (self-hosted Git, optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────
# Admin password for the Gitea host container ('task gitea:setup'). The user is
# GITEA_ADMIN_USER from lab.env (default 'giteaadmin'). If unset, setup uses a
# default and warns. Used to create the repo and push to it; the repo itself is
# public, so Argo CD needs no credential to read it.
# GITEA_ADMIN_PASSWORD=
